##Disturbed, terrified and moved, a Wuhan man stays in Yunnan for 24 days

WMSYGSDR

Function introduction, each line has the earnest person, again the ordinary person also has the extraordinary story. Huazhong University of Science and Technology Press Official non-fiction story platform, the story of the people will meet here.

”

1

It was a new day, and the curtains were drawn. The Sun, the size of a red egg, rose over Dian Lake. The Sun's rays broke through the clouds and spread a golden hue over the water, nearby, white black-headed gulls fly over the lake. Stretch, today is the 14th day of quarantine, tomorrow you can be free.

I was one of the many people from Wuhan who were stranded in Yunnan because of the COVID-19.

The company held its annual meeting on January 18 and officially closed on January 19. My family flew from Wuhan to Lijiang on the evening of the 19th as planned. Although we had heard about the unidentified pneumonia before, but we did not attach much importance to it. First, there was not a lot of media coverage. Second, it was said that it originated from the south China Seafood Market. We were in Guanggu, so far away, we thought it would not spread to us Third, the Spring Festival in Yunnan was planned two months ago, air tickets, hotels are also booked.

Along the way, the two little guys are the happiest, sitting in the window seat of the plane, looking at the stars in the sky with novelty.

Last Spring Festival, our family of six spent six days in Hainan, driving all over the coastal cities of Hainan, playing with children in the fine white sand of Sanya, to enjoy the sunset on the sea with my lover, to see the ancient salt pans of 1,000 years, to experience Mr. Dongpo's magnanimity at Danzhou College, and to spend New Year's Eve at Boao. Seeing the sky full of fireworks, tasting the local delicacies, and seeing CCTV New Year's Gala happily at the hotel as a family, we decided to stay out for the next Spring Festival!

After doing my homework, I decided not to drive myself, mainly because it was easier and time-saving to take the train between the cities of Lijiang, Dali and Kunming.

On the plane, I imagined enjoying a leisurely life in Dayan ancient town, basking in the sun, visiting the ancient city, going to Jade Dragon Snow Mountain to play in the snow, making a wish in Erhai Lake, Cangshan, feeding the black-headed Gulls in Dian Lake... We had no idea at the time that we were going to have an extraordinary spring festival and a strange psychological experience.

The dark-skinned, polite, and thoughtful, he kept telling us about the sights of Lijiang's ancient city.

On the first day (the 20th) , we walked freely in the ancient city, saw the popular Hanfu and Poncho, and bought a suit for the girl who loves beauty, she is cute and playful on the old city's slate roads, in front of Nakhi People's signature buildings, and by the slowly flowing, clear waters of the river.

Some tourists have started wearing masks in the old town. Although they are not taken seriously psychologically, we bought a pack just to be safe.

2

The next day, we went to Lashi Sea for a ride on the ancient tea horse road, and the third day, we went to Jade Dragon Snow Mountain for a Snow Day. During the break, I also watched the news and friends'circle. There are more and more reports about the new type of pneumonia in Wuhan. Many friends asked me if I was in Wuhan. I was also happy to say that I had already come out to travel and just hid for a few days.

On the way to Xueshan, the tour guide knew that we were from Wuhan. Talking about pneumonia, he said that he had asked someone to buy some cordyceps, which were said to help prevent pneumonia. It seems that ordinary people have started to pay attention to this epidemic.

The line in Jade Dragon Snow Mountain on the main ropeway lasted nearly two hours. The line moved slowly. We were all wearing masks, but in retrospect it was scary to think that if any of the tourists were carrying COVID-19, the chances of infection would be high in that case.

The more I followed the news, the more I began to worry, especially when I saw how many people had died of COVID-19. From the snow down, I feel cold body, plus two days ago are up early, no rest, worry about whether they have also been, the more I think the more uneasy, feel breathing a bit uncomfortable. Wife says she's scared of herself, but she's probably still got a reaction.

The next day, the discomfort was gone. In the news, people from other provinces are starting to look at people coming out of Wuhan in a different light. After consulting with our family, we decided to change our itinerary for the last few days. Instead of going to Kunming, we would return to Wuhan from Dali or Lijiang ahead of time.

News reports said Wuhan had started to restrict travel, and I laughed and said it was a good thing we were out early. On the morning of the 23rd, we caught the train to Dali. We changed seats with the others. The family sat in a box with six people. We talked about pneumonia.

3

Arriving in Dali, we managed to book a hotel for two nights. Seeing the Hubei a parked in front of the hotel, I joked with my wife that we weren't alone. Behind a small couple also saw the car, loudly said: "Ah, there is Wuhan's car, do not call the police! " We heard, the heart click, very bad taste.

There was a pharmacy outside the hotel, and we wanted to buy more masks, and as soon as we said we were out, we panicked. Fortunately, in Dali ancient city to buy a mask, in-laws are not used to wear, will often take down, they are born and bred in Wuhan, speech is still in Wuhan, by the wife a lot of contempt.

I feel sad, when Wuhan people go out so low-key, do not dare to expose their identity, we are ordinary people, but also victims Ah.

With the flood of news about the outbreak on Wechat, I began to worry about whether we could go back to Wuhan. Sure enough, we soon learned that flights from Lijiang and Dali to Wuhan had been cancelled.

On this day, when the city of Wuhan was closed, I realized that things were getting a little serious.

4

On New Year's Eve, we went to butterfly Spring by coach. When the ticket inspector took the temperature, he saw our ID card and said that we were from Wuhan and were the key test subjects. There was a shock in my heart, an embarrassment and a panic that a secret had been told. Although our body temperature is normal, but in the heart of the anxiety has long spread, the pleasure of playing has also lost. Back to the hotel early, we still spent a happy new year's Eve, eat a rich New Year's dinner.

We decided to change our itinerary again and go to Shuanglanggu town for two days or more to see how things develop. The first morning of the first online call for a car to double corridor town, on the car not long, master and tour guide small Zhao heard we are Wuhan people. Xiao Zhao repeatedly stressed that he is a professional tour guide, the kind of certificate, the guests are treated equally, he did not because we are from Wuhan and what disfavor.

He suggested we charter his car for a day trip to Erhai Lake, and finally get us to Shuanglang. The first attraction of a day's visit is met with a wall and the garden is closed. In the old town of Xizhou, we tasted Xizhou Baba in two flavors, sweet Baba made of rose sugar, which I still remember.

We appreciate the "Three Square one wall, four five courtyards, Horse Turret"-style residential characteristics, and pay attention to the price of others also let me marvel.

Zhao took us to a tourist demonstration village near Erhai Lake. We enjoyed the most beautiful scenery in Erhai Lake. The Unified White Wall, the Blue Sky, the various forms of clouds and their reflections in the water, as well as the occasional passing of a few seagulls, the water edge twists and turns of the old trees, together constitute a beautiful landscape, it temporarily soothed our emotions.

At that moment, I felt that I had enjoyed the most beautiful scenery since my trip. For more than ten minutes, we were free and happy.

From time to time, Xiao Zhao's group of tour guides would pop up all kinds of news, saying that the Shuanglang scenic area would soon be closed, which immediately put us out of our interest. The tour guide also saw our thoughts, and ended the day's tour ahead of schedule and sent us to our destination.

5

When we got to the front desk, we saw our ID card. Several people at the front desk exchanged glances quickly. One person shook his head and said that they were not allowed to receive tourists from Wuhan.

We're all panicking. It's almost night. Where are the kids gonNA live. The boss hesitated and whispered quietly that he would let us stay one night and then leave. Most of the evening, my wife and I are looking for people everywhere, looking for information, to see where can live, how can go back to Wuhan.

There are warm-hearted colleagues, friends, relatives have given a lot of advice and information, in times of adversity, a true friend, very moved me. His wife joined the Wechat Group of stranded Hubei People in Yunnan and found hotels in Dali and Kunming willing to receive Hubei People.

Finally, we decided to go to Kunming, thinking about returning to Wuhan convenient. At ten o'clock the next morning, the innkeeper said that the scenic spot was closed and could not receive visitors. He told us to move out immediately.

I bought a train ticket to Kunming, but can not contact willing to send us to Dali Station Master, they see my Wuhan phone number, are not to come. Finally begged a master, said countless good words, finally agreed to send us. All the way we didn't want to see Erhai Lake, we just wanted to go to Kunming!

After taking my temperature and entering the waiting hall, I felt relieved and thought it would be better to go to Kunming. I could stay at the hotel for a few days and return to Wuhan. On the Internet, I saw many people in Wuhan buying trains that had stopped in Wuhan before. They bought one more station or one less station and got off at Wuhan Station.
At this time we really want to go back to Wuhan early, even if the isolation at home is also willing to, did not realize the severity of the Wuhan epidemic.

On the train sultry, plus wearing a mask, the mood is also nervous, I feel their bodies are hot, dazed, I must not get sick ah!

Smooth check-in hotel, the owner is Wuhan people, to our Hubei residents built a wechat group. I am happy to say that I have finally found a big family. In Times of crisis, I have experienced the great love of the world. The experiences of other people in the group are also similar. Other hotels do not accept it. After seeing the messages sent by the boss, everyone gets together. For this, the boss has turned away guests from other provinces.

These days the epidemic is one day after another, my mood also along with the fluctuations, like a roller coaster, in this day finally calm down. I had the best night's sleep I've had in days. I told everyone who cared about us that I was safe and that I could finally have a good rest for a few days.

Wake up the next day, open wechat group, sudden change, climb the building to see the information, the mood suddenly bad, the original few Wuhan tourists did not check out procedures, left the hotel early in the morning, take the high-speed rail back to Wuhan.

Now the local police station gets nervous, seals off the whole building, nobody gets in or out. The other hotels in the building were out of business and blamed the Wuhan owner for the abuse and even the beating of the store manager.

The owner of the hotel took in more than 100 people from Hubei Province because of his love of hometown and his blood, but he didn't expect something unexpected to happen. We're restricted. We can't go out. We have to order in. I have some regrets, did not seize the opportunity to return to Wuhan, fleeting, now impossible.

6

On the night of the 28th, after an uneasy two day wait, the local community arranged several buses, most of them on board, and we were taken to the workers'sanatorium in Haikou, Fujian. Living conditions are not bad, since the arrival of a comfortable, we sleep peacefully.

I know. We can't leave yet. We're quarantined. Two days before I moved in, I wondered which day I would start to calculate the quarantine, the 19th from Wuhan, the 26th from Kunming, and the 28th from the workers'sanatorium. When could we go home?

The situation in Wuhan is getting worse and worse, with many new cases every day and no sign of a decline. Slowly, I stopped Random Thoughts. The nine million people in Wuhan were at home and contributing to the country. We had shelter, food, and what more could we want?

The 150 Hupeis are treated to milk and yogurt for breakfast at the Haikou Street office and the workers'sanatorium, not to repeat the main course, but sometimes to local dishes such as pork ribs, lotus root soup and fruit after dinner.

In the dining bag, often can also see to cheer up the words, read especially heartwarming. We have people take our temperature twice a day, help people with special drug needs to buy drugs, designated two supermarkets to provide us with personalized supplies delivery services.

Especially reassuring and warm to me is the establishment of the Temporary Party branch in the street office and the industrial and therapeutic hospital. We have more than 20 party members joining. We have held two branch committees in a special form and learned from the important speeches of the state leaders on the prevention and control of the epidemic, we're more reassured.

Days of isolation, every day to brush the phone, information overwhelming, rumors flying, refuting rumors will soon follow up. Wuhan's actual situation, more and more clear, I understand why to close the city, why the decision to close the city, academician Zhong will shed tears, because he knows Wuhan people will make great sacrifices.

In the early days of the outbreak, too many people suffered and even lost their lives because they could not be hospitalized or treated. Unfortunately, the loss of life, not the total number of daily reports, but one by one was a fresh life.

There are so many things that bring tears to my eyes every day, and I am truly grateful to everyone who helped Hubei fight the epidemic, no matter where they came from or what jobs they held. These twenty days, I have enough time to accompany my family, it is countless people in front of tears, sweat, blood to pay, we have a peaceful and peaceful life, I will cherish every day.

Yesterday it rained heavily in Dian Lake, and after the rain the rainbow came as expected, and almost everyone of US rushed to the window to marvel at the brilliant colours of the rainbow. A friend of mine who has not contacted me for more than 10 years left me a message on Qq, "waiting for the clouds to clear and the fog to disperse. ". Yes, the clouds have cleared, rainbows have come, and we have waited for that day.

February 11, Dian Lake.

-END-
